.TH "devm_counter_register" 9 "devm_counter_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_counter_register \- Resource-managed counter_register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_counter_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct counter_device *const counter "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to allocate counter_device for
.IP "counter" 12
pointer to Counter to register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed counter_register. The Counter registered with this function is
automatically unregistered on driver detach. This function calls
counter_register internally. Refer to that function for more information.

If an Counter registered with this function needs to be unregistered
separately, devm_counter_unregister must be used.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error number on failure.
